                <h1>When Did Daylight Saving Time Start?</h1>
                <p>Daylight Saving Time (DST) began in the early 20th century to make better use of daylight and conserve energy. It was first implemented in Germany during World War I in 1916, followed by other countries. In the U.S., it was established nationwide in 1918 but has seen various changes since then, including its current schedule.</p>
